{"lastModified":1762337406705,"uri":"c::27074328118::vessel::47cb8120-a8de-11ef-93f4-c151b7193f38","yachtType":["Motor"],"description":"Operating Area: Croatia\n\nWith a length of 49 meters, it is an impressive luxury cruise ship. 18 spacious air-conditioned cabins with private toilets can accommodate up to 36 guests onboard. Lounge bar (VIP salon), jacuzzi, spacious sun deck, reception, modern kitchen, restaurant, and hostess on board. This mini-cruise ship is built in 2021 and operates deluxe cruise tours in Croatia. Cabins are located on the lower and main decks and are a mix of Double or Twin berths. Lastavica is stylishly decorated with modern, spacious indoor and outdoor social areas for guests to relax, dine or drink. Up top, there is a spacious sundeck area with loungers and a hot tub. A swim platform at the rear of the boat allows guests to swim, snorkel or make use of the onboard water sports activities.\n\nThis luxury cruise ship offers a choice of different custom-made itineraries to some of the Adriatic’s top spots including Split, Vis, Brač, Dubrovnik, Hvar, Zadar, Lastovo nature park. Explore the spectacular National Parks Mljet, Kornati, and medieval towns along the Adriatic coast, or take a swim at the famous Zlatni Rat beach. See the natural phenomenon that is the Blue Cave in Biševo and visit Korčula, the birthplace of Marco Polo. With so much to see and do, there is an itinerary to suit everyone.","blueprint":{"name":"SWALLOW","images":["/media/media::image::a::vessel::47cb8120-a8de-11ef-93f4-c151b7193f38::assets::7b882290-50d9-11f0-93d9-c9a3efbbfc51/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::47cb8120-a8de-11ef-93f4-c151b7193f38::assets::7b89d040-50d9-11f0-93d9-c9a3efbbfc51/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::47cb8120-a8de-11ef-93f4-c151b7193f38::assets::7b853c60-50d9-11f0-93d9-c9a3efbbfc51/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::47cb8120-a8de-11ef-93f4-c151b7193f38::assets::7b92f800-50d9-11f0-93d9-c9a3efbbfc51/{imageV